This email constitutes a request under the Illinois Freedom of Information Act, 5 ILCS 140, for the following records:
Any and all policies, instructions, memos, manuals, rulebooks, training materials, guidelines, or emails since January 1, 2009 pertaining to FOIA procedures.  Examples of records include: 
(a) documents (e.g. manuals, guidelines, rulebooks, training materials, etc.) that guide FOIA officers on how to receive, interpret, identify, search, or process requests or appeals;
(b) internal memos and/or emails with updates, changes, or reminders about FOIA compliance policies or procedures;
(c) materials with case studies, scenarios, or other information used for training, teaching, or guiding FOIA officers;    
(d) statistics about the number of requests received, processed, complied with, appealed, and overturned;
(e) any documents (e.g. memos, guidelines, emails, lists, databases, spreadsheets, etc.) pertaining to handling or processing submissions from (i) specific individuals, organizations, or companies or (ii) types or categories of actors and entities.

